\hypertarget{class_open_x_l_s_x_1_1_x_l_shared_strings}{}\doxysection{Open\+XLSX\+::XLShared\+Strings Class Reference}
\label{class_open_x_l_s_x_1_1_x_l_shared_strings}\index{OpenXLSX::XLSharedStrings@{OpenXLSX::XLSharedStrings}}


This class encapsulate the Excel concept of Shared Strings. In Excel, instead of havig individual strings in each cell, cells have a reference to an entry in the Shared\+Strings register. This results in smalle file sizes, as repeated strings are referenced easily.  




{\ttfamily \#include $<$XLShared\+Strings.\+hpp$>$}

\doxysubsection{Detailed Description}
This class encapsulate the Excel concept of Shared Strings. In Excel, instead of havig individual strings in each cell, cells have a reference to an entry in the Shared\+Strings register. {\footnotesize\ttfamily void Open\+XLSX\+::\+XLShared\+Strings\+::clear\+String (\begin{DoxyParamCaption}\item[{uint64\+\_\+t}]{index }\end{DoxyParamCaption})}



Clear the string at the given index. 


\begin{DoxyParams}{Parameters}
{\em index} & The index to clear. \\
\hline
\end{DoxyParams}
\begin{DoxyNote}{Note}
There is no \textquotesingle{}delete\+String\textquotesingle{} member function, as deleting a shared string node will invalidate the shared string indices for the cells in the spreadsheet. Instead use this member functions, which clears the contents of the string, but keeps the XMLNode holding the string. 
\end{DoxyNote}
